s, fifteen state titles and sixteen city championships. The Edward R. Murrow HS chess team's success has been chronicled in the book [[The Kings of New York]], by sportswriter [[Michael Weinreb]]. [[The Kings of New York]] follows the 2005 championship-winning season of the Murrow Team. It was reviewed positively in the March 4, 2007 NY Times Book Review.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/04/books/review/Kaplan.t.html|title=The Kings of New York - By Michael Weinreb - Books - Review|last=Kaplan|first=James|date=2007-03-04|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-25|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> The team was personally congratulated by President Bush in the Oval Office on December 15, 2004. A movie, based on \"The Kings of New York\" will begin production sometime in 2014.{{citation needed|date=May 2015}}\n\n==Student demographics==\nThere are 4,000+ students in the school as of the 2016-2017 school year. The ethnic breakdown of the school is 28% [[White people|White]] (non-Hispanic), 23% [[Black people|Black]] or [[African American]], 26% [[Asian people|Asian]], 21% [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] and 0.2% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]]. The student/teacher ratio is 30/1. The Department of Education has released the annual Progress Reports for all high schools and Murrow.{{citation needed|date=May 2015}}\n\n==Programs and activities==\n\n===Theater===\n\nMurrow has a theater program that explores all the collaborative components of theater. Students learn all the aspects of theater including acting, technical theater, musical theater, and theater management. According to a [[New York Times]] article, student voluntarily stay after school work with theater program even on weekends and free periods. Students were painting the backdrop for the school's annual musical ''Into the Woods''. Students prepare months before the musical. In the [[costume]] department, freshmen were busy sewing leaves and vines. Students were designing [[Stage lighting|lighting]] sets.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/13/nyregion/at-a-brooklyn-high-school-plenty-of-drama-before-the-curtain-goes-up.html|title=At a Brooklyn High School, Plenty of Drama Before the Curtain Goes Up|last=Stapinski|first=Helene|date=2016-11-11|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-25|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n=== Music===\n\nThe school has instrumental and vocal music programs that includes large ensemble, small ensemble, solo performance, and musicianship. Both programs require audition. For instrumental music, students may audition for more than one instrument. Students must bring their own instruments (except piano, tuba, double bass, harp, percussion and guitar amplifiers, which are provided by the school) and a copy of the music they are performing. For vocal music, students must perform a song without accompaniment.\n\nIn 2018, the schools music technology program hosted the Second Annual Music x Tech Fest, a show in which students and alumni performed original songs and presented music videos that they had created to raise money for charity.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://brooklyneagle.com/articles/2018/03/15/music-x-tech-fest-gives-murrow-hs-kids-chance-to-shine/|title=Music x Tech Fest gives Murrow HS kids chance to shine|date=2018-03-15|website=Brooklyn Eagle|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref>\n\n=== Fine and Visual Arts ===\n\nThe school has a discipline-based visual art program which includes studios in drawing, painting, sculpture, mixed media, animation, digital media, photography, fashion, art history, and portfolio development. In 2014, the school renovated it's TV studio.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/education/best-high-schools-edward-murrow-high-school-adds-tv-studio-article-1.1973945|title=Best High Schools: Edward R. Murrow High School fills its namesake\u2019s large footprints|last=AGISH|first=MERAL|website=nydailynews.com|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref>\n\n===Bilingual programs===\n\nThe school has [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Chinese language|Chinese]] transitional bilingual program open to English language learners. Classes in two major content areas are taught in English and the other language.\n\n===Sports===\n\nThe school offers a variety of [[Varsity team|varsity]] and [[Junior varsity team|junior varsity]] sports. These sports include [[badminton]], [[bowling]], [[Cross country running|cross country]], [[golf]], [[soccer]], [[table tennis]] and [[volleyball]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.psal.org/profiles/school-profile.aspx#21565|title=School Profile|website=www.psal.org|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> The school shares an athletic field with [[Midwood High School]].\n\n===Extracurricular activities===\n\nThe school offers extracurricular activities including academic teams, art shows, [[chess]], [[community service]]s, [[concert]]s and productions, [[digital media]]. [[key club]], [[mock trial]], [[moot court]], [[music technology]], [[National Honor Society]], [[robotics]], s!ng, [[Stagecraft|technical theater]] and virtual enterprise.\n\n==Notable alumni==\n*[[Darren Aronofsky]] - Director\n*[[Joey Badass]] - Rapper, Actor\n*[[Jean-Michel Basquiat]] - Artist\n*[[Salvijus Bercys]] - International Chess Master\n*[[Capital STEEZ]] - Rapper\n*[[Nyck Caution]] - Rapper, Actor\n*[[CJ Fly]] - Rapper\n*[[Yvette Clarke]] - US Congresswoman\n*[[Jerry Colonna (financier)|Jerry Colonna]] - Noted Internet Investor, Philanthropist\n*[[Dyme-A-Duzin]] - Rapper\n*[[Arabella Field]] - Actress\n*[[Anna Hahn (chess player)|Anna Hahn]] - US Women's Chess Champion\n*[[Eliza Hittman]] - Director\n*[[Jason Katims]] - TV Writer and producer\n*[[Irina Krush]] - US Women's Chess Champion\n*[[Alex Lenderman]] - International Chess Grandmaster and 2005 World under 16 Champion\n*[[Lil Mama]] - Rapper\n*[[Zoe Lister-Jones]] - Actress\n*[[Javier Mu\u00f1oz (actor)|Javier Mu\u00f1oz]] - Actor ([[In the Heights]]; [[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]] - Broadway)\n*[[Adepero Oduye]] - Actress<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/brooklyn/sunset-park-sundance-brooklyn-teen-role-adepero-oduye-article-1.136470|title=From Sunset Park to Sundance: B'klyn teen actress' star on the rise|website=NY Daily News|access-date=2016-03-29}}</ref>\n*[[Edward Quist]] - Director and artist\n*[[UberFacts|Kris Sanchez]] - Founder of [[UberFacts]]\n*[[Jennifer San Marco]] - [[Goleta, California|Goleta]] postal facility shooting\n*[[Dave Sardy|David Sardy]] - Producer, Movie score\n*[[Jeffrey Alan Schechter]] - Screenwriter and producer\n*[[Marcia Schofield]] - Keyboard player, The Fall\n*[[Michael Spiller]] - TV Director and Producer\n*[[Peter Steele]] - Singer/Song Writer.  [[Type O Negative]] and [[Carnivore]]\n*[[Marisa Tomei]] - Actress\n*[[Richard Velazquez]] - [[PepsiCo]] Executive and first automotive designer at [[Porsche]] AG (Germany) of Puerto Rican descent\n*[[Adam Yauch]] of the [[Beastie Boys]] - Rapper\n*Jennifer San Marco - Perpetrator of the 2006 [[Goleta postal facility shootings]]\n\n==Transportation==\n\nThe school can be reached by [[public transportation]], including the [[New York City Subway]]'s [[Avenue M station]] ({{NYCS trains|Brighton local}}) as well as [[MTA Regional Bus Operations]]' {{NYC bus link|B6|B9|B11|B49|B68|BM1|BM3|BM4|prose=y}} routes.\n<ref>{{cite NYC bus map|B}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.ermurrowhs.org/ School Website]\n*[http://www.ermurrowhs.org/uploads/6/2/6/8/6268393/band_aid_2014.pdf Murrow Band-Aid (Schedule)]\n*[http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/tag/saul-bruckner/ Saul Bruckner NYT Obituary]\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1974]]\n[[Category:Public high schools in Brooklyn|Murrow]]\n", "name_user": "Joel.Miles925", "label": "safe", "comment": "this is here twice", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_R._Murrow_High_School"}
{"title_page": "Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder", "text_new": "{{ infobox officeholder\n| name        = Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder\n| native_name        = \u2d4e\u2d53\u2d43\u2d30\u2d4e\u2d37 \u2d31\u2d3b\u2d4f\u2d59\u2d44\u2d49\u2d37 \u2d30\u2d62\u2d5c \u2d49\u2d37\u2d37\u2d3b\u2d54 <br/> \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0639\u064a\u062f \u0623\u064a\u062a \u0625\u064a\u062f\u0631\n| native_name_lang   = \n|image = Bensaid Idder.JPG\n| office      =\n| term_start  = \n| term_end    =\n| predecessor = \n| birth_date  = 1 July 1925\n| birth_place = [[Chtouka A\u00eft Baha Province|Chtouka A\u00eft Baha]], [[Morocco]]\n| nationality = [[Morocco|Moroccan]]\n| spouse = \n| party       = [[Istiqlal Party]] (1945\u20131959)<br/>[[National Union of Popular Forces]] (1959\u20131970s)<br/>[[Organization for the Popular Democratic Action]] (1983\u20132002)<br/>[[Unified Socialist Party (Morocco)|Unified Socialist Party]] (Since 2002)\n}}\n'''Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder''' (in Berber:\u2d4e\u2d53\u2d43\u2d30\u2d4e\u2d37 \u2d31\u2d3b\u2d4f\u2d59\u2d44\u2d49\u2d37 \u2d30\u2d62\u2d5c \u2d49\u2d37\u2d37\u2d3b\u2d54 \u2013 Born: July 1, 1925 in [[Chtouka A\u00eft Baha Province|Chtouka A\u00eft Baha]]) is a Moroccan politician and activist, and is considered one of Morocco's leftist symbols. Ait Idder started his activism first against [[French Protectorate in Morocco]], and was one of the founders and leaders of the [[Moroccan Army of Liberation]]. After Morocco's independence, Ait Idder opposed the system in place, especially the [[Hassan II of Morocco|king Hassan II]].\n\nBensaid Ait Idder was co-founder of several leftist political movements and parties in the independent Morocco, including:[[National Union of Popular Forces]], [[Harakat 23 Mars]], [[Organization for the Popular Democratic Action]] and the [[Unified Socialist Party (Morocco)|Unified Socialist Party]].\n\n==Early life==\nMohamed Bensaid Ait Idder was born in 1925 in Tin Mansour, in the Berber-speaking province of Chtouka A\u00eft Baha, in [[Sous]], Morocco. After finishing his primary studies, he moved to Marrakesh in 1945 to start university studies. There, he adopted nationalistic ideas and worked together with anti-colonial activists in Marrakesh, including [[Abdallah Ibrahim]] and [[Mohamed Basri]].<ref>[https://www.hespress.com/%D8%B2%D9%88%D9%88%D9%85/69829.html Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Hespress(2013) - in Arabic]</ref>\n\n==Political Activism==\n* In 1955, Bensaid Ait Idder joined the [[Moroccan Army of Liberation]] in the south, and started participating in the armed resistance against the French and Spanish forces in Morocco. Their efforts were crushed after the ''Operation \u00c9couvillon'' in 1958.\n* In 1959, Ait Idder, together with several modernist activists, left the [[Istiqlal Party]] and participated in the creation of the [[National Union of Popular Forces]].\n* In 1963, and after the ''July 1963 Conspiracy'', Bensaid Ait Idder was condemned to death. He escaped to Algeria at that time.\n* Following the [[1965 Moroccan riots]], Ait Idder founded with several [[Marxism\u2013Leninism|Marxist\u2013Leninist]] activists the [[Harakat 23 Mars]], a movement spreading revolutionary ideas in Morocco.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.net/encyclopedia/icons/2015/5/11/%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%86-%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A2%D9%8A%D8%AA-%D8%A5%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B1 Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Al Jazeera (2015) - in Arabic.]</ref>\n* In 1981 Ait Idder received a royal pardon and came back to Morocco, where he founded the ''Organization for the Popular Democratic Action'' party, that was a legal party, and with which he sat in the [[Parliament of Morocco|parliament]] from 1984 to 2007.<ref>[https://www.alaraby.co.uk/politics/2017/10/23/%D8%B2%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A3%D9%8A%D8%AA-%D8%A5%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B1-4-1 Charismatic Leaders of Morocco - Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Al Araby (2017) - in Arabic.]</ref>\n* In 2002, the Organization for the Popular Democratic Action merged with several leftist parties to create the [[Unified Socialist Party (Morocco)|Unified Socialist Party]], for which Bensaid Ait Idder is an emblematic figure until today.\n* In 2015, Ait Idder received a royal distinction from the [[Mohammed VI of Morocco|king Mohamed 6]].<ref>[https://www.jeuneafrique.com/mag/255200/politique/maroc-bensaid-ait-idder-lancien-opposant-a-hassan-ii-decore/ Maroc : Bensa\u00efd A\u00eft Idder, l\u2019ancien opposant \u00e0 Hassan II d\u00e9cor\u00e9 - Jeune Afrique (2015) - in French.]</ref>\n\n==Books==\nIn 2001, Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder published a book entitled ''Epic pages of the Liberation Army in the Moroccan South'',<ref>[https://books.google.co.ma/books/about/%D8%B5%D9%81%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AA_%D9%85%D9%86_%D9%85%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%A9_%D8%AC%D9%8A%D8%B4_%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA.html?id=9D4_AQAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y Epic pages of the Liberation Army in the Moroccan South - Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Google Books.]</ref> relating his experience with the Moroccan Liberation Army between 1955 and 1958.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Berber Moroccans]]\n[[Category:Berber rebels]]\n[[Category:Moroccan Berber politicians]]\n[[Category:Moroccan dissidents]]\n[[Category:Moroccan exiles]]\n[[Category:Moroccan rebels]]\n[[Category:Moroccan revolutionaries]]\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox officeholder\n| name        = Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder\n| native_name        = \u2d4e\u2d53\u2d43\u2d30\u2d4e\u2d37 \u2d31\u2d3b\u2d4f\u2d59\u2d44\u2d49\u2d37 \u2d30\u2d62\u2d5c \u2d49\u2d37\u2d37\u2d3b\u2d54 <br/> \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0639\u064a\u062f \u0623\u064a\u062a \u0625\u064a\u062f\u0631\n| native_name_lang   = \n|image = Bensaid Idder.JPG\n| office      =\n| term_start  = \n| term_end    =\n| predecessor = \n| birth_date  = 1 July 1925\n| birth_place = [[Chtouka A\u00eft Baha Province|Chtouka A\u00eft Baha]], [[Morocco]]\n| nationality = [[Morocco|Moroccan]]\n| spouse = \n| party       = [[Istiqlal Party]] (1945 - 1959)<br/>[[National Union of Popular Forces]] (1959 - 1970's)<br/>[[Organization for the Popular Democratic Action]] (1983 - 2002)<br/>[[Unified Socialist Party (Morocco)|Unified Socialist Party]] (Since 2002)\n}}\n'''Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder''' (in Berber:\u2d4e\u2d53\u2d43\u2d30\u2d4e\u2d37 \u2d31\u2d3b\u2d4f\u2d59\u2d44\u2d49\u2d37 \u2d30\u2d62\u2d5c \u2d49\u2d37\u2d37\u2d3b\u2d54 - Born: July 1, 1925 in [[Chtouka A\u00eft Baha Province|Chtouka A\u00eft Baha]]) is a Moroccan politician and activist, and is considered as one of Morocco's leftist symbols. Ait Idder started his activism first against [[French Protectorate in Morocco]], and was one of the founders and leaders of the [[Moroccan Army of Liberation]]. After Morocco's independence, Ait Idder opposed the system in place, especially the [[Hassan II of Morocco|king Hassan II]].\n\nBensaid Ait Idder was co-founder of several leftist political movements and parties in the independent Morocco, including:[[National Union of Popular Forces]], [[Harakat 23 Mars]], [[Organization for the Popular Democratic Action]] and the [[Unified Socialist Party (Morocco)|Unified Socialist Party]].\n\n==Early life==\nMohamed Bensaid Ait Idder was born in 1925 in Tin Mansour, in the Berber speaking province of Chtouka A\u00eft Baha, in [[Sous]], Morocco. After finishing his primary studies, he moved to Marrakesh in 1945 to start university studies. There, he adopted nationalistic ideas and worked together with anti-colonial activists in Marrakesh, including [[Abdallah Ibrahim]] and [[Mohamed Basri]].<ref>[https://www.hespress.com/%D8%B2%D9%88%D9%88%D9%85/69829.html Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Hespress(2013) - in Arabic]</ref>\n\n==Political Activism==\n* In 1955, Bensaid Ait Idder joined the [[Moroccan Army of Liberation]] in the south, and started participating in the armed resistance against the French and Spanish forces in Morocco. Their efforts were crushed after the ''Operation \u00c9couvillon'' in 1958.\n* In 1959, Ait Idder, together with several modernist activists, left the [[Istiqlal Party]] and participated in the creation of the [[National Union of Popular Forces]].\n* In 1963, and after the ''July 1963 Conspiracy'', Bensaid Ait Idder was condemned to death. He escaped to Algeria at that time.\n* Following the [[1965 Moroccan riots]], Ait Idder founded with several [[Marxism\u2013Leninism|Marxist\u2013Leninist]] activists the [[Harakat 23 Mars]], a movement spreading revolutionary ideas in Morocco.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.net/encyclopedia/icons/2015/5/11/%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%86-%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A2%D9%8A%D8%AA-%D8%A5%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B1 Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Al Jazeera (2015) - in Arabic.]</ref>\n* In 1981 Ait Idder received a royal pardon and came back to Morocco, where he founded the ''Organization for the Popular Democratic Action'' party, that was a legal party, and with which he sat in the [[Parliament of Morocco|parliament]] from 1984 to 2007.<ref>[https://www.alaraby.co.uk/politics/2017/10/23/%D8%B2%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%83%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%BA%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%B3%D8%B9%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A3%D9%8A%D8%AA-%D8%A5%D9%8A%D8%AF%D8%B1-4-1 Charismatic Leaders of Morocco - Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Al Araby (2017) - in Arabic.]</ref>\n* In 2002, the Organization for the Popular Democratic Action merged with several leftist parties to create the [[Unified Socialist Party (Morocco)|Unified Socialist Party]], for which Bensaid Ait Idder is an emblematic figure until today.\n* In 2015, Ait Idder received a royal distinction from the [[Mohammed VI of Morocco|king Mohamed 6]].<ref>[https://www.jeuneafrique.com/mag/255200/politique/maroc-bensaid-ait-idder-lancien-opposant-a-hassan-ii-decore/ Maroc : Bensa\u00efd A\u00eft Idder, l\u2019ancien opposant \u00e0 Hassan II d\u00e9cor\u00e9 - Jeune Afrique (2015) - in French.]</ref>\n\n==Books==\nIn 2001, Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder published a book entitled ''Epic pages of the Liberation Army in the Moroccan South'',<ref>[https://books.google.co.ma/books/about/%D8%B5%D9%81%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AA_%D9%85%D9%86_%D9%85%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%A9_%D8%AC%D9%8A%D8%B4_%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA.html?id=9D4_AQAAIAAJ&redir_esc=y Epic pages of the Liberation Army in the Moroccan South - Mohamed Bensaid Ait Idder - Google Books.]</ref> relating his experience with the Moroccan Liberation Army between 1955 and 1958.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Berber Moroccans]]\n[[Category:Berber rebels]]\n[[Category:Moroccan Berber politicians]]\n[[Category:Moroccan dissidents]]\n[[Category:Moroccan exiles]]\n[[Category:Moroccan rebels]]\n[[Category:Moroccan revolutionaries]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "replaced: -  \u2192  \u2013  (4), 1945 \u2013 1959 \u2192 1945\u20131959 (3), etc.; gr", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohamed_Bensaid_Ait_Idder"}
{"title_page": "Roswell, New Mexico (TV series)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 science fiction drama television series}}\n{{For|the 1999 TV series|Roswell (TV series)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = Roswell, New Mexico\n| image              = Roswell-new-mexico-title-card.jpg\n| image_upright      = \n| image_size         = \n| image_alt          = \n| caption            =\n| show_name_2        = \n| genre              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n* [[Science fiction]]\n* [[Mystery fiction|Mystery]]\n}}\n| based_on           = {{Based on|''[[Roswell High]]''|[[Melinda Metz]]}}\n| developer          = {{Plainlist|\n* Carina Adly MacKenzie\n}}\n| starring           = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jeanine Mason]]\n* [[Nathan Dean Parsons]]\n* Michael Vlamis\n* Lily Cowles\n* [[Tyler Blackburn]]\n* [[Heather Hemmens]]\n* [[Michael Trevino]]\n* [[Trevor St. John]]\n* Karan Oberoi\n* [[Amber Midthunder]]\n}}\n| narrated           = Jeanine Mason\n| theme_music_composer = \n| opentheme          = \n| endtheme           = \n| composer           = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Michael Suby]]\n* Dennis Smith\n}}\n| country            = United States\n| language           = English\n| num_seasons        = 2<!-- Or num_series. Increment when new seasons/series begin. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| num_episodes       = 19<!-- Value is incremented when new episodes air. See template documentation for more info. -->\n| list_episodes      = #Episodes\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Carina Adly MacKenzie\n* Kevin Kelly Brown\n* Justin Falvey\n* Darryl Frank\n* [[Lawrence Bender]]\n* [[Julie Plec]]\n* [[Steven Spielberg]]\n}}\n| location            = \n| cinematography      = Alan Caso\n| editor              = {{Plainlist|\n* Christopher Nelson\n* Tyler L. Cook\n}}\n| camera              = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime             = 40-43 minutes\n| company             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Amblin Television]]\n* My So-Called Company\n* Bender Brown Productions\n* [[CBS Television Studios]]\n* [[Warner Bros. Television]]\n}}\n| distributor         = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]\n| network             = [[The CW]]\n| picture_format      = [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format        = \n| first_aired         = {{Start date|2019|1|15}}\n| last_aired          = {{End date|present}}\n| related             = ''[[Roswell (TV series)|Roswell]]''\n| website             = https://www.cwtv.com/shows/roswell-new-mexico/\n| production_website  = \n}}\n\n'''''Roswell, New Mexico''''' is an American [[science fiction]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] television series, named after the city of [[Roswell, New Mexico]], developed by Carina Adly Mackenzie for [[The CW]] that debuted as a midseason entry during the [[2018\u201319 United States network television schedule|2018\u201319 television season]] on January 15, 2019. The series is the second television adaptation of the ''[[Roswell High]]'' book series by [[Melinda Metz]].\n\nIn April 2019, the series was renewed for a second season,<ref name=\"S2Renewal\" /> which premiered on March 16, 2020.<ref name=\"S2AirDate\">{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/11/08/cw-premiere-dates-katy-keene-roswell-legends-of-tomorrow/ |title=The CW Sets Katy Keene Series Premiere Date, Plus New Seasons of Roswell and Legends of Tomorrow |last=Swift |first=Andy |date=November 8, 2019 |accessdate=November 8, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108200639/https://tvline.com/2019/11/08/cw-premiere-dates-katy-keene-roswell-legends-of-tomorrow/ |archive-date=November 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, The CW renewed the series for a third season.<ref name=\"S3Renewal\" />\n\n==Series overview==\nAfter returning to her hometown of [[Roswell, New Mexico]], the daughter of undocumented immigrants discovers her teenage crush is an alien who has kept his unearthly abilities hidden his entire life. She protects his secret as the two reconnect, but when a violent attack points to a greater alien presence on Earth, the politics of fear and hatred threaten to expose him.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n* [[Jeanine Mason]] as Liz Ortecho, a jaded biomedical researcher and the daughter of undocumented immigrants.<ref name=\"Mason\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/roswell-jeanine-mason-cast-the-lead-the-cw-reboot-pilot-1202292358/ |title='Roswell': Jeanine Mason Cast As the Lead Of the CW Reboot Pilot |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 16, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180515005720/https://deadline.com/2018/02/roswell-jeanine-mason-cast-the-lead-the-cw-reboot-pilot-1202292358/ |archive-date=May 15, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Nathan Dean Parsons]] (credited as Nathan Dean in season 2) as Max Evans, a natural born leader and dedicated Roswell deputy sheriff, who has kept his true identity a secret for years.<ref name=\"Parsons\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/roswell-nathan-parsons-lily-cowles-michael-vlamis-tyler-blackburn-heather-hemmens-cast-the-cw-reboot-pilot-1202311948/ |title='Roswell': Nathan Parsons, Four More Cast In the CW Reboot Pilot |last=Petski |first=Denise |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 5, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509120726/http://deadline.com/2018/03/roswell-nathan-parsons-lily-cowles-michael-vlamis-tyler-blackburn-heather-hemmens-cast-the-cw-reboot-pilot-1202311948/ |archive-date=May 9, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* Michael Vlamis as Michael Guerin, a troubled but brilliant alien drifter, who survived a traumatic childhood and is trying to find a way to escape Earth.<ref name=\"Parsons\" />\n* Lily Cowles as Isobel Evans, an alien and sister to Max, who keeps her true identity a secret by living her life with grace and enthusiasm.<ref name=\"Parsons\" />\n* [[Tyler Blackburn]] as Alex Manes, a military veteran with his fair share of physical and psychological trauma. Alex prepares to abandon his dreams and the possibility of a future with the man he loves to succumb to his father's expectations.<ref name=\"Parsons\" />\n* [[Heather Hemmens]] as Maria DeLuca, Liz and Rosa's best friend, who is a bartender at a popular saloon and oblivious to the existence of aliens.<ref name=\"Parsons\" />\n* [[Michael Trevino]] as Kyle Valenti, a doctor and the son of the town sheriff, who learns about horrible things that have happened in his family's past.<ref name=\"Trevino\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2018/03/06/roswell-reboot-michael-trevino-cast-the-cw/ |title=Roswell Reboot: The Vampire Diaries' Michael Trevino Joins Pilot Cast |last=Roots |first=Kimberley |work=[[TVLine]] |date=March 6, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180510075040/http://tvline.com/2018/03/06/roswell-reboot-michael-trevino-cast-the-cw/ |archive-date=May 10, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Trevor St. John]] as Jesse Manes, Alex's father, a [[senior master sergeant]] with a secret to hide.<ref name=\"John\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/roswell-casts-trevor-st-john-megan-ferguson-mixtape-1202336433/ |title='Roswell' Casts Trevor St. John; Megan Ferguson Joins 'Mixtape' |last=Petski |first=Denise |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 12, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180512112905/http://deadline.com/2018/03/roswell-casts-trevor-st-john-megan-ferguson-mixtape-1202336433/ |archive-date=May 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* Karan Oberoi as Noah Bracken (season 1; guest season 2), Isobel's charming, devoted lawyer husband, who senses a secret in his wife.<ref name=\"Oberoi\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/roswell-casts-karan-oberoi-max-jenkins-most-likely-to-1202353652/ |title='Roswell' Casts Karan Oberoi; Max Jenkins Joins 'Most Likely To' |last=Petski |first=Denise |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 27, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180512113100/http://deadline.com/2018/03/roswell-casts-karan-oberoi-max-jenkins-most-likely-to-1202353652/ |archive-date=May 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Amber Midthunder]] as Rosa Ortecho (season 2; recurring season 1), Liz's older sister, who was killed in a car crash while high on drugs, killing two girls in the process. Liz gradually comes to realize that Max may have been involved in her death.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nypost.com/2018/06/14/father-daughter-duo-are-among-rare-native-american-actors-in-hollywood/ |title=Father/daughter duo are among rare Native American actors in Hollywood |first=Lauren |last=Sarner |date=June 14, 2018 |access-date=August 2, 2018 |work=New York Post |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180802011511/https://nypost.com/2018/06/14/father-daughter-duo-are-among-rare-native-american-actors-in-hollywood/ |archive-date=August 2, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Recurring===\n* Rosa Arredondo as Michelle Valenti, Kyle's mother, who succeeded her late husband, Jim Valenti, as sheriff of Roswell.\n* Carlos Compean as Arturo Ortecho, Liz's father, who runs the Crashdown Cafe diner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2018/07/23/roswell-new-mexico-sdcc-secret-event/ |title='Roswell, New Mexico' Crash-Landed Into San Diego with a Sold-Out Secret Event |website=[[Bleeding Cool]] |last=Johnston |first=Rich |date=July 23, 2018 |access-date=July 30, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180730234809/https://www.bleedingcool.com/2018/07/23/roswell-new-mexico-sdcc-secret-event/ |archive-date=July 30, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Riley Voelkel]] as Jenna Cameron, Max's fellow deputy and partner.<ref name=\"Voelkel\">{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/08/01/the-originals-riley-voelkel-roswell-new-mexico/ |title=The Originals star Riley Voelkel joins Roswell, New Mexico |date=August 1, 2018 |access-date=August 1, 2018 |work=Entertainment Weekly |last1=Highfill |first1=Samantha |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801190656/http://ew.com/tv/2018/08/01/the-originals-riley-voelkel-roswell-new-mexico/ |archive-date=August 1, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Sherri Saum]] as Mimi DeLuca, Maria's mother, who suffers from an undiagnosed mental illness.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/976808/roswell-new-mexico-welcomes-the-fosters-star-sherri-saum |title=Roswell, New Mexico Adds The Fosters Star Sherri Saum |date=October 12, 2018 |website=E! Online |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026025154/https://www.eonline.com/news/976808/roswell-new-mexico-welcomes-the-fosters-star-sherri-saum |archive-date=October 26, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Claudia Black]] as Ann Evans, Max and Isobel's adoptive mother.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2018/10/25/roswell-new-mexico-spoilers-claudia-black-cast-the-cw-reboot/ |title=Roswell, New Mexico Casts Originals Baddie as Max and Isobel's Mother |first1=Andy |last1=Swift |first2=Andy |last2=Swift |date=October 25, 2018 |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124201852/https://tvline.com/2018/10/25/roswell-new-mexico-spoilers-claudia-black-cast-the-cw-reboot/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* Dylan McTee as Wyatt Long, the brother of one of the girls Rosa Ortecho killed, who harbors a grudge against her family.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/dylanmctee/ |title=Dylan McTee (@dylanmctee) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos |website=www.instagram.com |accessdate=January 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508021043/https://www.instagram.com/dylanmctee/ |archive-date=May 8, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nIn January 2018, The CW ordered the show to pilot, with [[Julie Plec]] set to direct.<ref name=\"PilotOrder\">{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/roswell-reboot-p-greg-berlanti-rob-thomas-6-cw-pilot-orders-record-total-of-9-pilots-1202274800/ |title='Roswell' Reboot, Projects Produced By Greg Berlanti & Rob Thomas Among 6 CW Pilot Orders For Record Total Of 9 Pilots |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=January 30, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403112355/https://deadline.com/2018/01/roswell-reboot-p-greg-berlanti-rob-thomas-6-cw-pilot-orders-record-total-of-9-pilots-1202274800/ |archive-date=April 3, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Production companies involved with the pilot include [[Amblin Television]], Bender Brown Productions, [[CBS Television Studios]] and [[Warner Bros. Television]]. The CW ordered the show to series on May 11, 2018.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/the-cw-picks-up-charmed-roswell-reboots-tvd-originals-offshoot-ilegacies-n-the-dark-greg-berlanti-pilot-to-series-1202388840/ |title=The CW Picks Up 'Charmed' & 'Roswell' Reboots, 'TVD'/'Originals Offshoot, 'In The Dark' & Greg Berlanti Pilot To Series |last=Petski |first=Denise |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=May 11, 2018 |accessdate=May 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180516060159/http://deadline.com/2018/05/the-cw-picks-up-charmed-roswell-reboots-tvd-originals-offshoot-ilegacies-n-the-dark-greg-berlanti-pilot-to-series-1202388840/ |archive-date=May 16, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On April 24, 2019, The CW renewed the series for a second season.<ref name=\"S2Renewal\">{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |title='All American', 'In The Dark', 'Roswell, New Mexico', 'The 100' Renewed; The CW To Bring Back Record 14 Series Next Season |url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/all-american-in-the-dark-roswell-new-mexico-the-100-renewed-the-cw-1202601250/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=April 24, 2019 |date=April 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424182117/https://deadline.com/2019/04/all-american-in-the-dark-roswell-new-mexico-the-100-renewed-the-cw-1202601250/ |archive-date=April 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> On January 7, 2020, the series was renewed for a third season.<ref name=\"S3Renewal\">{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2020/01/07/the-cw-renewed-shows-2020-list-riverdale-flash/ |title=CW Renews Riverdale, Batwoman, Roswell, Black Lightning Plus 9 Others |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |work=TVLine |date=January 7, 2020 |accessdate=January 7, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108032431/https://tvline.com/2020/01/07/the-cw-renewed-shows-2020-list-riverdale-flash/ |archive-date=January 8, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nOn February 16, 2018, Jeanine Mason was cast in the lead role of Liz Ortecho.<ref name=\"Mason\" /> In early March, the rest of the cast was filled out, with Nathan Parsons as Max Evans, Lily Cowles as Isobel, Michael Vlamis as Michael Guerin, Tyler Blackburn as Alex Manes, Heather Hemmens as Maria DeLuca, and Michael Trevino as Kyle Valenti. Karan Oberoi was cast in the final series regular role of Noah Bracken on March 27, 2018.<ref name=\"Parsons\" /><ref name=\"Trevino\" /><ref name=\"Oberoi\" /> [[Trevor St. John]] was cast in a recurring role as Alex's father on March 12, 2018.<ref name=\"John\" /> In April 2019, Amber Midthunder, who played Liz's older sister Rosa in a recurring capacity in the first season, was promoted to the main cast for the second season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/04/25/roswell-new-mexico-season-2-amber-midthunder-rosa-series-regular/ |title=Roswell Promotes Amber Midthunder to Series Regular for Season 2 |work=TVLine |date=April 25, 2019 |access-date=April 25, 2019 |last=Swift |first=Andy |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425213723/https://tvline.com/2019/04/25/roswell-new-mexico-season-2-amber-midthunder-rosa-series-regular/ |archive-date=April 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming for the pilot took place in [[Albuquerque, New Mexico|Albuquerque]] and [[Santa Fe, New Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/tv-pilot-locations-2018-new-york-los-angeles-rankings-1202311512/ |title=Pilot Locations 2018: New York Business Booming, Chicago Gains As Atlanta Slips |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 9, 2018 |accessdate=May 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180506032758/http://deadline.com/2018/03/tv-pilot-locations-2018-new-york-los-angeles-rankings-1202311512/ |archive-date=May 6, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Production on the pilot begin on March 14, 2018,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/cadlymack/status/973449413602435072?s=17 |title=You guys. We roll camera on cowboys and aliens tomorrow. Holy shit. #Roswell |date=March 13, 2018 |access-date=May 20, 2018 |work=[[Twitter]] |first1=Carina Adly |last1=MacKenzie}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/cadlymack/status/973795167332372481?s=17 |title=Extraordinary first day spent in the company of extraordinary women. Our exec producers, director, first AD, scripty, coordinating producer, network exec, camera operator, actresses, assistants -- you are so inspiring. #Roswell. Dudes were also present doing dude stuff. |date=March 14, 2018 |access-date=May 20, 2018 |work=Twitter |first1=Carina Adly |last1=MacKenzie}}</ref> and ended on March 30, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bg9O5P4Br_V/? |title=The end |date=March 30, 2018 |access-date=July 8, 2018 |work=[[Instagram]] |first1=Tyler |last=Blackburn}}</ref> The rest of the episodes began filming August 13, 2018, in [[Las Vegas, New Mexico|Las Vegas]], New Mexico; Nevada; and Santa Fe, New Mexico.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ruidosonews.com/story/news/local/community/2018/08/08/roswell-television-series-filming-first-season-new-mexico/937656002/ |title=\"Roswell\" television series filming first season in New Mexico |website=Ruidoso News |access-date=2019-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190523201440/https://www.ruidosonews.com/story/news/local/community/2018/08/08/roswell-television-series-filming-first-season-new-mexico/937656002/ |archive-date=May 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n\n| color1     = #DA812F\n| link1      = #Season 1 (2019)\n| episodes1  = 13\n| start1     = {{Start date|2019|1|15}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2019|4|23}}\n\n| color2     = #3B240B\n| link2      = #Season 2 (2020)\n| episodes2  = 13\n| start2     = {{Start date|2020|3|16}}\n| end2       = \n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2019)===\n{{Episode table |background=DA812F |overall=5 |season=5 |title=25 |titleR=<ref name=\"TFC\" /> |director=15 |writer=25 |airdate=12 |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Roswell, New Mexico Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/roswell-new-mexico/listings/ |website=The Futon Critic |accessdate=January 26, 2019}}</ref> |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |prodcode=8 |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Julie Plec]]\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|t=Carina Adly Mackenzie}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|1|15}}\n |ProdCode        = T33.01005\n |Viewers         = 1.51<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-15-2019/ |title='New Amsterdam' adjusts down: Tuesday final ratings |last=Welch |first=Alex |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=January 16, 2019 |accessdate=January 16, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190117035332/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-15-2019/ |archive-date=January 17, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = After losing her research grant, biomedical scientist Liz Ortecho returns to her hometown of Roswell to work in her family's diner. There, she reconnects with her high-school crush, deputy sheriff Max Evans, her old friend Maria DeLuca, and her former boyfriend Kyle Valenti. When a gunman shoots and fatally wounds Liz, Max is forced to use his healing abilities to save her, leaving him weakened until his sister, Isobel, nurses him back to health. She and Max's younger brother, Michael, confront Max over the wisdom of using his abilities to save Liz's life. Max becomes overburdened by guilt and decides to tell Liz who he truly is, unaware that Liz has secretly taken a DNA sample from him and analyzed it. He takes her to the [[Roswell UFO incident|site]] of the \"birth\" of his siblings and him, and reveals that his powers also create a temporary psychic link between Liz and him, allowing her to view his memories. Kyle, having uncovered Liz's analysis, is taken to \"Project Shepherd\", a government initiative to track extraterrestrials. At their high-school reunion, Isobel warns Max to break things off with Liz before she learns the truth behind her sister Rosa's death.\n |LineColor       = DA812F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = So Much for the Afterglow\n |DirectedBy      = [[Tim Andrew]]\n |WrittenBy       = Eva McKenna & Carina Adly MacKenzie\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|1|22}}\n |ProdCode        = T48.10102\n |Viewers         = 1.21<ref name=\"1.02\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-22-2019/ |title='The Flash' and 'Celebrity Big Brother' adjust up, 'Kids Are Alright' adjusts down: Tuesday final ratings |last=Welch |first=Alex |work=TV by the Numbers |date=January 24, 2019 |accessdate=January 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190125020450/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-jan-22-2019/ |archive-date=January 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Liz receives a new grant in [[San Diego]], allowing her to leave town. Despite learning that his ancestor was killed by an alien in 1947, Kyle refuses to assist Project Shepherd. Max and his partner Jenna identify a local, Wyatt Long, as the man who shot Liz, and embarrass him in a shooting contest. Isobel and Michael try to intimidate Liz, but Max defends her. Kyle agrees to help Liz find her sister's hidden autopsy report, which reveals that she did not die in an accident. At the same time, she learns from her psychic bond that Max was with Rosa on the night she died. Wyatt and his friends assault Liz's father; Max beats Wyatt and nearly kills him with his abilities before his siblings intervene. Conflicted by Max's actions saving her father, Liz asks him to tell her when he last saw Rosa, and he lies. Michael strikes up a relationship with Alex Manes, a veteran working near his trailer, while Max has sex with Jenna at her house. Liz decides to stay in Roswell, telling Kyle that she intends to bring her sister's murderer to justice, even if it is Max.\n |LineColor       = DA812F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Tearin' Up My Heart\n |DirectedBy      = Geoff Shotz\n |WrittenBy       = Rick Montano & Vincent Ingrao\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|1|29}}\n |ProdCode        = T48.10103\n |Viewers         = 1.27<ref name=\"1.03\">{{cite web |url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/the-flash-adjusts-up-tuesday-final-ratings/ |title='The Flash' adjusts up: Tuesday final ratings |last=Welch |first=Alex |work=TV by the Numbers |date=January 30, 2019 |accessdate=January 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131040602/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/the-flash-adjusts-up-tuesday-final-ratings/ |archive-date=January 31, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n |ShortSummary    = Under the guise of treating him, Liz tries to scientifically determine if Max killed Rosa. Isobel and Michael, fearing the consequences of Liz learning