st_aired = {{start date|2010|2|21}}\n| last_aired = present\n}}\n\nOriginally anchored by [[Pia Arcangel]] and [[Jiggy Manicad]], the weekend edition of ''24 Oras'' premiered on February 21, 2010 on the network's Saturday and Sunday night line up replacing ''[[GMA Weekend Report]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=24 Oras Weekend premieres this Sunday, February 21 |url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/5612/24-oras-weekend-premieres-this-sunday-february-21 |accessdate=April 26, 2018 |work=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]] |date=February 20, 2012}}</ref> On April 21, 2018, Manicad left the show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2018/04/22/1808377/jiggy-manicad-leaves-media-next-level-public-service |title=Jiggy Manicad leaves media for \u2018next level\u2019 of public service {{!}} Philstar.com |website=philstar.com |accessdate=June 11, 2018}}</ref> In August 2018, [[Ivan Mayrina]] became an anchor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/showbiznews/news/43076/ivan-mayrina-co-anchors-24-oras-weekend/story |title=Ivan Mayrina co-anchors '24 Oras Weekend' |website=www.gmanetwork.com |accessdate=August 16, 2018}}</ref> Arcangel and Mayrina currently serve as anchors.\n\n===Anchors===\n* [[Pia Arcangel]] {{small|(since 2010)}}\n* [[Ivan Mayrina]] {{small|(since 2018)}}\n* Nelson Canlas {{small|(since 2013, ''Chika Minute'')}}\n\n;Former anchors\n* [[Jiggy Manicad]] {{small|(2010\u20132018)}}\n* [[Grace Lee]] {{small|(2010\u20132012, ''Chika Minute'')}}\n* [[Luane Dy]] {{small|(2010\u20132013, ''Chika Minute'')}}\n* Cata Tibayan {{small|(2013\u20132018, ''Chika Minute'')}}\n\n===Ratings===\nAccording to [[AGB Nielsen Philippines]]' Mega Manila household television ratings, the premiere of ''24 Oras Weekend'' earned a 18.4% rating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/news/local/24798/agb-mega-manila-tv-ratings-feb-19-22-panday-kids-and-pilipinas-got-talent-make-strong-impact-on-thei |title=AGB Mega Manila TV Ratings (Feb. 19-22): Panday Kids and Pilipinas Got Talent make strong impact on their debut |author=Santiago, Erwin |date=February 23, 2010 |accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year\n! Awards\n! Category\n! Recipient\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2018\n| [[32nd PMPC Star Awards for Television]]\n| Best Female Newscaster\n| [[Pia Arcangel]]\n| {{nom}}\n!\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[33rd PMPC Star Awards for Television]]\n| Best Male Newcaster\n| [[Ivan Mayrina]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/146277/33rd-star-awards-for-television-names-tv-queens-pmpc-bares-nominees |title=33rd Star Awards for Television names TV Queens; PMPC bares nominees |work=Pep.ph |language=en |author=Dimaculangan, Jocelyn |date=September 22, 2019 |accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Regional versions==\n*  ''24 Oras Amianan''\n* ''[[24 Oras Bikol]]''\n* ''24 Oras Central Visayas''\n* ''24 Oras Davao''\n* ''[[24 Oras Ilokano]]''\n* ''24 Oras North Central Luzon''\n* ''[[24 Oras Northern Mindanao]]''\n* ''24 Oras Southern Mindanao''\n* ''24 Oras Western Visayas''\n* ''[[Ratsada 24 Oras]]''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/shows/24oras}}\n* {{IMDb title|0764672}}\n\n{{24 Oras}}\n{{PhilNetworkEveningNewsShows}}\n{{PhilNetworkHourlyNewsBulletins}}\n{{GMA Network (current and upcoming original programming)}}\n{{GMA News and Public Affairs}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network news programs]]\n[[Category:GMA News and Public Affairs programs]]\n[[Category:Philippine television news programs]]\n[[Category:2004 Philippine television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000s Philippine television series]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Flagship evening news programs]]\n", "name_user": "Hotwiki", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAccolades:fixed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/24_Oras"}
